{# Jinja template for the repair agent's task string.
   Rendered by run_repair.py. Two RCA schemas feed this template:

   A) Legacy static/coverage-based RCA (list[per-test]):
      - rca_top1_files        : list[str]   (already test-file-filtered)
      - rca_top5_files        : list[str]
      - rca_evidence          : str         (compact, may be empty)
      - rca_confidence        : "high" | "low" | "missing"
      - repro_only_files      : list[str]   (in localizer but NOT in RCA top5)

   B) Dynamic debug-agent RCA (unified schema; preferred):
      - debug_reasoning             : str   ("" when unavailable or timed out w/o signal)
      - debug_suggested_fix         : str
      - debug_root_cause_files      : list[str]
      - debug_root_cause_functions  : list[str]
      - debug_transcript_tail       : str   (last 6 actions, tail-trimmed)
      - debug_timed_out             : bool
      - rich_symptom                : {file,lineno,exc_type,exc_msg} | None
      - rich_contract_impact        : {kind,summary,callers[],callers_truncated} | None
      - rich_propagation_frames     : list[{file,lineno,qualname,role}] | None
      - rich_related_non_code       : list[str] | None
      - rich_branch_observations    : list[{file,lineno,cond_text,arm_taken,locals_at_stop}] | None
      - rich_pdb_anomalies          : list[{file,lineno,expr,value_repr,tags}] | None

   Common:
      - problem_statement     : str
      - requirements          : str (may be empty)
      - interface             : str (may be empty)
      - repro_localizer_files : list[str]   (stage1 LLM localizer)
      - repro_localizer_funcs : list[str]

   When both RCA fields are empty (schema-B timed out, or schema-A missing),
   the prompt degrades to a baseline-style render (problem + requirements
   only) — injecting empty hints was proven to hurt more than help.
#}
