── Verification Requirements (read this BEFORE submitting) ──

The reproduction test that was attached is necessary but NOT sufficient. It
covers ONE failure mode of the issue. Your patch must satisfy the FULL
behavioral contract described in the PR description above, including any
clauses the repro test does not directly check.

Before submitting, you MUST do all of the following:

1. Re-read the entire PR description / "Expected Behavior" section above and
   build a checklist of every distinct behavior the issue requires.
2. For each item on that checklist, identify which line(s) of your patch
   satisfy it. If any item has no corresponding patch logic, you are not done.
3. Look for adjacent code paths in the same file/class that handle similar
   inputs — if the issue describes a general principle (e.g. "X must always
   imply Y"), make sure the principle holds in ALL such paths, not just the
   one the repro test happens to hit.
4. Double-check that the file you edited matches the workflow described in
   the issue. If the issue talks about workflow A but you patched a file in
   workflow B (e.g. patched the search API for an "import" bug), STOP and
   investigate the entry point of workflow A first.
5. Only after the checklist is fully covered should you create patch.txt and
   submit.

Do NOT stop just because the failing reproduction test turned green. A patch
that minimally flips the repro test red→green but leaves other parts of the
behavior contract unaddressed will fail the hidden test suite.
{%- endif %}
